cs.NE, cs.ET, cs.IT, cs.BI, cs.EM

The paper discusses the physical design of a molecular receiver, which involves aspects of nanoelectronics, biosensing, and communication theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which deals with the design and analysis of intelligent systems at the nanoscale. The second likely category is cs.ET (Emerging Technologies), which covers novel technologies and their applications, including nanoelectronics and biosensors. The third likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the fundamental limits and coding schemes of communication systems. The fourth likely category is cs.BI (Bioinformatics), which deals with the analysis and modeling of biological systems, including synthetic cells. The fifth likely category is cs.EM (Electromagnetism), which covers the theory and applications of electromagnetic fields, including their interaction with molecules and nanoscale devices.
